dc_description_s: This point data layer represents addresses for Waukesha County, Wisconsin in 2015. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, Waukesha_Addresses_2015.gdb. [The file was originally derived from the Addressing Maintenance System tabular database by joining it to the Tax Parcel feature class and creating a centroid. It was then updated to reflect the needs of E911 dispatch. Each address point is located on the main building of a parcel or the center of the parcel if no building exists. Mile Markers are posted at the locations of the actual signs. Non-addressed points (landmarks, points of interest, etc) are placed where deemed useful. The file also contains retired addresses that are no longer valid.]
uw_supplemental_s: This is an archived copy of the data held at UW-Madison. For the most recent version of this data, please visit: https://data-waukeshacounty.opendata.arcgis.com/
